were influencing the Corps to keep the water low in the Atchafalaya in order to squeeze out swamp fishermen like him, whose forebears were swamp fishermen. It is possible that the charge he was making was based on pure suspic
ion, but now that the structures were emplaced at Old River\emdash and the Corps had assumed charge of the latitude flow\emdash suspicion was one more force they had to try to control.
\par As we were heading back toward the landing, Bourque remarked, surprisingly, \'93It\rquote s good we have the levees. Before the levees, the crawfish, they was spread all over.\'94
\par For bait, for gasoline, and so forth, the cost of the day\rquote s run was seventy-five dollars. At the boat landing, Bourque sold the crawfish for three hundred and sixty. The
